WEBVTT

00:00.034 --> 00:03.700
The following message by Alistair Begg is made available by Truth For Life.

00:04.501 --> 00:08.468
For more information, visit us online at truthforlife.org.

00:10.511 --> 00:14.317
Romans chapter 8, and I'm going to read from verse 9 to 17.

00:17.081 --> 00:21.989
Paul continues from where we left it off yesterday, those who are in the flesh cannot please God.

00:22.630 --> 00:27.378
And then he says, you, however, are not in the flesh but in the Spirit.

00:27.746 --> 00:35.314
If, in fact, the Spirit of God dwells in you, anyone who does not have the Spirit of Christ does not belong to him.

00:35.354 --> 00:43.203
But if Christ is in you, although the body is dead because of sin, the Spirit is life because of righteousness.

00:44.204 --> 00:56.498
If the Spirit of him who raised Jesus from the dead dwells in you, he who raised Christ Jesus from the dead will also give life to your mortal bodies through his Spirit who dwells in you.

00:57.090 --> 01:04.018
So then, brothers and sisters, we are debtors not to the flesh, to live according to the flesh.

01:04.639 --> 01:11.547
For if you live according to the flesh, you will die, but if by the Spirit you put to death the deeds of the body you will live.

01:12.408 --> 01:16.253
For all who are led by the Spirit of God are sons of God.

01:17.094 --> 01:27.026
For you do not receive the Spirit of slavery to fall back into fear, but you have received the Spirit of adoption as sons by whom we cry, Abba Father.

01:27.490 --> 01:32.815
The Spirit Himself bears witness with our Spirit that we are children of God.

01:33.456 --> 01:45.367
And if children then heirs, heirs of God and fellow heirs with Christ provided we suffer with Him in order that we may also be glorified with Him.

01:46.768 --> 01:47.109
Amen.

01:47.449 --> 01:48.550
A brief prayer together.

01:51.112 --> 01:54.696
Father, we thank You again for the privilege of gathering in this way.

01:54.756 --> 01:56.978
We thank You for the opportunity

01:57.186 --> 01:59.870
to sing praise to you, the triune God.

02:00.751 --> 02:05.178
We acknowledge that while we're here, many of our loved ones and friends are far from us.

02:05.779 --> 02:10.386
Some of them are a burden to us because of the circumstances of life.

02:11.067 --> 02:21.042
And so even in this moment as we turn to the Bible, we seek to cast our burdens upon the Lord in the assurance that you care for us and will care for them.

02:21.864 --> 02:23.506
We pray, Lord, for those who

02:23.618 --> 02:27.865
will never in this lifetime ever experience anything like this at all.

02:28.426 --> 02:37.760
We think of the persecuted Christians throughout the world in North Korea, in Nigeria, in sub-Saharan Africa, and in many other places.

02:38.541 --> 02:41.726
And they are in Christ, and we are in Christ.

02:42.388 --> 02:45.412
And when they pray, they draw near to the throne of grace.

02:46.013 --> 02:48.958
And when we pray, we draw near to the throne of grace.

02:49.459 --> 02:51.602
Therefore, they and we

02:52.002 --> 02:55.427
are not and cannot be far apart.

02:55.948 --> 03:07.545
We commend them to you, and we pray that you will take your truth planted deep in us, shape and fashion us in the likeness of your Son, in whose name we pray.

03:08.306 --> 03:08.727
Amen.

03:09.508 --> 03:19.162
Beginning with verse 9, you will notice, if the text is open before you, that Paul moves from the third person to the second person.

03:20.103 --> 03:21.906
He has, up until verse 8,

03:22.146 --> 03:28.274
been saying these things in general terms, those who are, those who are, those who are.

03:28.875 --> 03:35.484
And now here in verse 9, he says, you, however, are not in the flesh.

03:36.526 --> 03:51.346
Speaking generally to those, and now very specifically to those to whom he writes, you, however, unlike those that I've just been referring to in the flesh, who cannot please God, are in the spirit.

03:51.842 --> 03:55.873
Now, there is something that you should notice immediately here, and you perhaps have.

03:55.934 --> 03:57.839
I'll just reinforce it for us.

03:57.859 --> 03:59.524
There are a number of synonyms here.

04:00.226 --> 04:04.498
And this is one of the places in people easily go wrong.

04:04.866 --> 04:07.250
especially in home Bible study groups.

04:07.610 --> 04:13.179
You notice this says, you ever are not in the flesh, but in the Spirit, if the Spirit of God dwells in you.

04:13.640 --> 04:25.659
And anyone who does not have the Spirit of Christ immediately somebody puts out their hand and says, excuse me, the first time he says it's the Spirit of God, and the second time he says it's the Spirit of Christ, what is going on here?

04:26.100 --> 04:28.183
And the answer is, these are synonyms.

04:28.744 --> 04:32.530
The Spirit of God, the Spirit of Christ is the exact same.

04:32.930 --> 04:38.355
The Spirit who is in you, here's another synonym, and Christ who is in you.

04:39.276 --> 04:53.410
It is very straightforwardly and important that we understand what we said yesterday that the Father, the Son, and the Holy Spirit are inseparable in their activity in the lives of the believers.

04:54.211 --> 05:01.138
The Father, the Son, and the Holy Spirit are eternally distinct in terms of their personal modes of being.

05:01.346 --> 05:06.312
The Father is not the Son, the Son is not the Spirit, the Spirit is not the Father.

05:06.593 --> 05:11.860
They are co-equal, they are co-eternal, and they are distinct in their eternal mode of being.

05:12.320 --> 05:15.464
But they are united in the work of redemption.

05:16.005 --> 05:22.834
And it is this work of redemption that Paul has been referencing since the very beginning of Romans.

05:23.106 --> 05:31.798
And I want to fix it in your mind that what the Father planned, the Son procured, and the Spirit of God, applies.

05:32.759 --> 05:36.724
And of course, what we're addressing here is life in the Spirit.

05:37.545 --> 05:42.952
That is the over-emphasis of all that follows in the verses that are before us.

05:43.573 --> 05:50.322
It's a reminder to us, excuse me, that genuine Christianity is not just a new set of beliefs,

05:50.530 --> 05:53.493
Nor is it a new pattern of behavior.

05:53.533 --> 05:57.678
It is actually a matter, a matter of belonging.

05:58.058 --> 06:00.541
You ever are not in the flesh, but in the spirit.

06:00.921 --> 06:08.410
If, in fact, the spirit of God dwells in you, anyone who does not have the spirit of Christ does not belong to him.

06:10.492 --> 06:19.602
God looks at us and he says to us essentially, sinner on account of all that my son has done, you

06:19.682 --> 06:22.346
belong to me, you belong to me.

06:22.386 --> 06:35.226
And the distinguishing mark of the Christian is the indwelling reality of the Holy Spirit, that the Holy Spirit comes to indwell the life of the Christian.

06:37.589 --> 06:42.176
Our life in Adam is the indwelling reality of the Spirit.

06:43.318 --> 06:48.626
And our lives continuing in Adam are lives that are disintegrating.

06:49.282 --> 06:56.090
But our life in Christ is the reality, not of the indwelling sin, but of the indwelling spirit.

06:57.131 --> 07:08.864
Now, as thankful as I am for the hymns we've sung, and for all the new hymns that we've been learning to sing, I confess to the fact that I have a measure of regret for the passage of some of the oldies.

07:09.565 --> 07:17.554
And as I come to a verse like this, I go immediately in my mind to the phraseology, which begins, Jesus, my Lord,

07:17.666 --> 07:22.855
will love me forever from him no power of evil can sever.

07:22.895 --> 07:29.306
He gave his life to ransom my soul, and now I belong to him.

07:30.508 --> 07:32.572
Now I belong to Jesus.

07:33.734 --> 07:42.930
Jesus belongs to me, and not for the years of time alone, but for eternity.

07:43.938 --> 07:50.066
that the relationship into which God and His grace as brought us in Jesus is eternal.

07:50.086 --> 07:59.297
Another one that I haven't sung since probably the 8th of June, thou art the sinner's friend.

08:00.599 --> 08:13.074
So I thy friendship claim, a sinner saved by grace when your sweet message came, mine, mine, mine,

08:13.698 --> 08:15.620
I know thou art mine.

08:16.441 --> 08:21.728
Savior, dear Savior, I know thou art mine.

08:22.589 --> 08:24.692
This is life in the Spirit.

08:25.332 --> 08:27.816
This is union with Christ.

08:28.376 --> 08:32.201
This is, if you like, basic Christianity.

08:33.162 --> 08:36.606
Authentic Christianity is not a mathematical formula.

08:36.627 --> 08:40.952
It is cerebral, but it is more than that.

08:41.613 --> 08:42.674
It is visceral.

08:43.362 --> 08:52.533
It is in the words of one of the old guys, the life of God in the soul of man, the life of God in the soul of man.

08:54.635 --> 08:59.200
When Paul writes to the Ephesians, he reminds them that they are light in the Lord.

08:59.601 --> 09:03.125
You were one's darkness, he says, but now you're light in the Lord.

09:03.505 --> 09:04.767
Where does the light come from?

09:05.288 --> 09:06.809
Jesus said, I am the light of the world.

09:06.829 --> 09:10.834
He who follows me will never walk in darkness, but we'll have the light of life.

09:11.106 --> 09:13.409
Where's that light come by the Holy Spirit?

09:13.970 --> 09:24.244
To the Colossians, he reminds us that we have been transferred from the kingdom of darkness into the kingdom of his beloved son.

09:24.284 --> 09:27.848
And that's the significance of verse nine.

09:28.709 --> 09:41.106
You, however, are not in the flesh, but in the spirit, if in Father's Spirit of God dwells in you, and then he puts it negatively, anyone who does not of the Spirit of Christ

09:41.186 --> 09:42.929
does not belong to him.

09:45.433 --> 09:47.436
I've been looking on this trip already.

09:47.537 --> 09:53.627
Every time I go to a different place, I look for football jerseys, football uniforms, as you call them.

09:54.088 --> 09:55.430
I mean soccer things.

09:56.071 --> 10:05.106
And I have a number of people who speak Spanish and to play on various teams that I've followed for a very long time.

10:05.218 --> 10:21.999
And those of you who know what I'm talking about will understand that when a person is transferred from one team to another, and of course it's true in American football as well, their identity actually shifts because they are no longer answerable to the people that they once were.

10:22.079 --> 10:23.040
They have now moved.

10:23.401 --> 10:26.344
So for example, Messi played for Barcelona.

10:26.545 --> 10:34.034
He played in the winning world, Argentinian World Cup team last time around, and then he transferred to Paris Saint-Germain.

10:34.466 --> 10:41.053
And so he appeared as a very different looking messy because he'd been transferred.

10:41.593 --> 10:43.896
He was no longer what he once was.

10:45.057 --> 10:47.159
And that's what the point is Paul is making.

10:47.500 --> 10:51.264
Years ago we had in Scotland a lady that came to our church.

10:51.724 --> 10:56.189
She had been high up in the nursing profession in England.

10:56.849 --> 10:58.932
Somewhere along the line she had become a Christian.

10:59.112 --> 11:01.234
She moved to Scotland

11:01.410 --> 11:04.054
for whatever reason and came to our church.

11:04.114 --> 11:13.969
And I remember talking with her one day, and she told me that some of her friends from her old nursing day had come up to Scotland and had got on the phone with her.

11:14.430 --> 11:20.479
And they said, hey, Miriam, you know, let's go out, let's go, hit the town, let's go, let's go, let's go.

11:20.900 --> 11:27.129
And when they sense the hesitancy in her voice, and then she says, you know, I don't think I want to do that.

11:27.810 --> 11:30.354
And one of them said, oh, come on now.

11:30.818 --> 11:33.402
That doesn't sound like the old Miriam to me."

11:33.422 --> 11:39.430
And she said, that's because I am no longer the old Miriam.

11:40.351 --> 11:51.326
And then she told them that she'd had a complete radical transformation, and the Spirit of God was now at work in her heart, and it made her a new person.

11:52.007 --> 12:00.338
It's vitally important, we recognize here, that Paul is not distinguishing between two different kinds of Christians.

12:00.930 --> 12:11.200
He's distinguishing between those who are regenerate and those who are unregenerate between two radically different folks.

12:11.921 --> 12:17.086
And there is no separable gospel of the Holy Spirit.

12:17.106 --> 12:18.468
It is the very same.

12:19.308 --> 12:23.953
So in verse 9, Paul is affirming the reality of the Spirit's presence.

12:24.354 --> 12:28.818
And then in verses 10 and 11, he begins to speak concerning the results.

12:29.058 --> 12:31.621
What happens when the Spirit invades a life?

12:32.522 --> 12:50.944
And it is very clear in verse 11, if the Spirit of him who raised Jesus from the dead dwells in you, he who raised Jesus from the dead will also give life to your mortal bodies through his Spirit who dwells in you.

12:50.965 --> 12:55.310
Now, it is this matter of our mortal bodies.

12:55.810 --> 12:56.792
We are mortal.

12:57.532 --> 12:58.834
Have you noticed that, haven't you?

12:59.170 --> 13:06.838
If you haven't, just look around a little bit about some of the people who are here, watch how we're walking and trying to get on.

13:07.319 --> 13:10.242
It is perfectly clear that Adam all died.

13:10.302 --> 13:12.424
The wages of sin is death.

13:13.766 --> 13:24.898
Physically, our house, if we think of our bodies as a house, physically our house is increasingly dilapidated.

13:25.418 --> 13:28.722
Whether you like that or not, I'm not looking at anyone in particular,

13:28.962 --> 13:32.206
But I'm just telling you that we are increasingly dilapidated.

13:33.008 --> 13:38.135
If we had nowhere else to go on the Bible than the Ecclesiastes 12, we would be greatly held, wouldn't we?

13:38.635 --> 13:49.330
Remember your grades or the days of your youth before the days of trouble come before you find yourself in the pharmacy going up aisles that you never, ever thought you would ever have to go on.

13:49.538 --> 14:00.434
When you find yourself asking, making inquiries, where do you have those shoulder things, or the thing you put on your elbow, and as someone else has for the knee, and do you have those expanding canes, and so on?

14:00.695 --> 14:03.118
And you're saying to yourself, how the world did we get like this?

14:03.439 --> 14:06.123
Well, because the house is crumbling.

14:07.285 --> 14:11.731
Inadequate inclusion, not enough on the top to meet the few we've got left on the bottom.

14:12.432 --> 14:17.140
We can't fall asleep, and yet we can wake up at the sound of birds.

14:17.981 --> 14:18.802
It's amazing.

14:19.138 --> 14:20.279
What is happening to us?

14:20.880 --> 14:22.942
We are dilapidated.

14:22.982 --> 14:24.663
And that's what he's saying.

14:25.004 --> 14:25.644
Here's the deal.

14:25.684 --> 14:27.086
You're dilapidated body.

14:27.126 --> 14:40.278
You need to understand that God who raised Christ from the dead will give life to your mortal bodies so that we have a life that is distinct from the actual physical frame of our lives.

14:40.839 --> 14:41.039
Right?

14:43.141 --> 14:43.501
Yes.

14:44.442 --> 14:48.466
I can't think you might have life that you might have in all of its fullness.

14:48.674 --> 14:50.416
Yeah, but what about my physical friend?

14:50.996 --> 14:53.059
What about the things that I'm dealing with?

14:53.079 --> 14:57.083
What about the things that are evident to me that I'm not going to last forever?

14:58.164 --> 15:00.186
I talk about Spanish people.

15:00.226 --> 15:04.991
I've been doing all my best Spanish in the last day or so, and it goes like this.

15:05.152 --> 15:14.061
It goes, Sergio Garcia, Olathabal, Alcaraz, and Buenas Notus.

15:14.081 --> 15:14.962
That's the end of it.

15:15.714 --> 15:24.887
But because I was thinking about Spanish golfers, it reminded me of Savvy Ballesteris, and as you know, he died of a brain tumor.

15:26.088 --> 15:33.539
And toward the end of his life, he was honest enough in an interview with a golf magazine to reflect on what he was facing.

15:33.659 --> 15:34.560
This is what he said.

15:35.702 --> 15:41.911
For everything in life, there is always a beginning and an end.

15:42.892 --> 15:44.434
This is the tough part.

15:45.026 --> 15:50.993
the most difficult thing when you see that it's coming, the end.

15:52.836 --> 15:54.077
Now, this is not to be morbid.

15:55.679 --> 16:00.545
Again, Ecclesiastes, death is the destiny of every man.

16:00.585 --> 16:04.470
The living must take this to heart.

16:05.451 --> 16:14.482
It is better to go to a funeral than to go to a pizza party because now we are framing our existence

16:14.562 --> 16:17.665
within the confines of what we know to be true.

16:17.685 --> 16:21.789
And without God and without hope in the world, it is a tyranny.

16:22.209 --> 16:23.310
It is a disaster.

16:24.151 --> 16:28.535
It is pushed back by the comedians because there is no ability to face it.

16:29.176 --> 16:34.441
Woody Allen is the archetypal nihilist of the 20th and 21st century.

16:34.761 --> 16:36.823
And he thinks he can laugh it off, but he can't.

16:37.504 --> 16:39.446
It's not that I'm afraid to die, he says.

16:39.766 --> 16:43.730
It's just that I don't want to be there when it happens, which is funny.

16:43.906 --> 16:44.847
But it's not funny.

16:46.068 --> 16:51.273
And he goes on to say, you know, I don't want to live on in the minds of my friends.

16:52.014 --> 16:55.537
I want to live on in my apartment, which makes perfect sense.

16:56.278 --> 16:57.299
It makes perfect sense.

16:57.739 --> 17:00.742
Now, what is the difference that comes to us in Jesus?

17:01.323 --> 17:05.226
Well, it is the reality of life in the Holy Spirit.

17:06.447 --> 17:13.394
Death is ours because of sin, but the Spirit is life because of righteousness.

17:14.530 --> 17:27.794
And all of us must know this to one degree or another, either vicariously in enterings of the lives of others, or by being made aware of it in the experience of our own earthly pilgrimage.

17:28.635 --> 17:39.314
Indeed, those who face such things have often proved to be the greatest encouragement to those of us who have only wondered about such things.

17:40.130 --> 18:09.586
Some years ago, I was speaking up in the northern part of California at a conference, and a lady came to me, I think I'd been doing two Corinthians four, you know, outwardly we're wasting away, but inwardly we're being renewed day by day, and she came to me and she told me that a friend of hers had told her of a situation where another friend was suffering through brain cancer and the treatments of brain cancer

18:09.698 --> 18:10.959
he was hospitalized.

18:12.301 --> 18:37.048
And his Christian testimony was such that the nurse, the night nurse on duty, leaving the report for the attending physician in the morning, wrote in the thing a critical comment, Mr. X appears to be inappropriately joyful, inappropriately joyful.

18:37.308 --> 18:39.250
There's no explanation for this.

18:39.426 --> 18:42.749
save life in the Spirit.

18:42.769 --> 18:48.134
That man was living in light of what Paul is telling us here in verse 11.

18:49.416 --> 19:02.208
It's another reminder to his incidentally in passing that as Christians, we do not believe simply in the immortality of the soul, but we believe in the resurrection of the body.

19:02.228 --> 19:08.754
That's why I think it's important that he actually refers to your mortal

19:08.866 --> 19:09.507
bodies.

19:10.928 --> 19:21.660
Because one of the marks of the unregenerate, the person who doesn't know Jesus, is a sort of defiance in the face of mortality.

19:22.961 --> 19:38.738
And here the identification of our mortal bodies shows that it is the same bodies that we as believers now possess that will be made alive in Christ in the resurrection.

19:40.002 --> 19:41.745
Now you say, how are you going to work all that out?

19:41.825 --> 19:42.968
I can't work it all out.

19:43.649 --> 19:45.953
I retreat to hymnity when I can't work it out.

19:46.915 --> 19:54.209
The hymn that begins written by Richard Baxter, the Puritan, Lord, it belongs not to my care whether I live or die.

19:54.229 --> 19:57.715
He means by that not I don't care if I live or die.

19:57.796 --> 20:01.202
He means that's not my department, that's your department.

20:01.282 --> 20:05.888
All the days of my life were written in his book before one of them came to be Psalm 139.

20:05.908 --> 20:08.731
So he says, I don't care.

20:09.132 --> 20:11.054
It's not to my department whether I'll ever die.

20:11.335 --> 20:14.939
And then the hymn goes on eventually against to the point which I find a tremendous help.

20:15.240 --> 20:18.444
It goes like this, my knowledge of that life is small.

20:19.225 --> 20:20.867
The eye of faith is dim.

20:21.868 --> 20:27.435
It is enough that Christ knows all and I shall be with him.

20:27.475 --> 20:29.778
What else do you need to know?

20:30.050 --> 20:30.791
What do you need us to know?

20:31.131 --> 20:32.393
Letting all your hearts be troubled.

20:32.433 --> 20:33.354
You believe in God.

20:33.434 --> 20:36.217
Jesus says to the disciples, you believe also in me.

20:36.237 --> 20:40.261
I wouldn't tell you that I'm going to prepare a place where you can trick you.

20:40.301 --> 20:45.647
And if I go and prepare a place, I will come again and receive you unto myself.

20:45.907 --> 20:47.129
The you, Peter.

20:47.509 --> 20:48.610
The you, John.

20:48.890 --> 20:49.932
The you, Sally.

20:50.152 --> 20:50.973
The you, Ruth.

20:51.653 --> 20:52.074
The you.

20:53.115 --> 20:54.476
This is Christianity.

20:54.957 --> 20:56.459
This is life in the spirit.

20:57.079 --> 20:59.602
Life now in a crumbling body.

21:00.098 --> 21:03.262
And life then, in the presence of Christ.

21:03.363 --> 21:06.567
Ray Arland does a wonderful little piece on this that I made a note of.

21:06.607 --> 21:11.614
He says, everything this sad life steals from us, God will restore.

21:11.634 --> 21:24.252
There is not one ounce of you that will end up in the trash bin of the universe, accept your sins, which you want to leave behind anyway.

21:24.272 --> 21:25.233
I found that pretty good.

21:25.854 --> 21:28.658
Now, along with this, this reality,

21:28.834 --> 21:33.359
There comes results, and there comes responsibility, verse 12.

21:33.759 --> 21:34.841
We have an obligation.

21:35.401 --> 21:37.544
So then, what are you saying, Paul?

21:37.984 --> 21:40.767
Well, brothers and sisters, we're debtors.

21:40.787 --> 21:44.171
Debtors, not to the flesh, to live according to the flesh.

21:44.892 --> 21:48.756
He repeats himself, because if you live according to the flesh, you will just die.

21:48.856 --> 21:52.941
But if by the Spirit you put to death the deeds of the body, you will live.

21:54.042 --> 21:57.906
Remember, we described flesh yesterday as human nature.

21:58.050 --> 22:01.594
corrupted, directed, and controlled by sin.

22:02.895 --> 22:07.500
But now we have an obligation that people don't like obligation, incidentally.

22:08.201 --> 22:16.770
In fact, there's a dirt, there's a four-letter word that is not very prevalent in contemporary Christianity, and it's the word duty, what you call duty.

22:17.511 --> 22:18.632
But it's actually duty.

22:19.233 --> 22:22.196
And so, D-U-T-Y, duty.

22:23.798 --> 22:26.641
No, there's not... Why are you talking to us about duty?

22:26.741 --> 22:27.442
I thought we...

22:27.714 --> 22:31.978
We're all free and we could please ourselves and go where we want to go and do where we want to go.

22:32.338 --> 22:34.681
No, that's just because you haven't been reading your Bible.

22:35.281 --> 22:38.704
You were once controlled by the downward drag of sin.

22:39.285 --> 22:55.640
You are now being controlled by the liberating reality of the Spirit of Christ, and it is entirely in Congress to think that we would allow ourselves to continue in the things that we have been saved from by the work of redemption.

22:56.321 --> 22:57.362
In Congress,

22:57.570 --> 23:01.475
to be slaves to the things from which the Holy Spirit has set us free.

23:02.737 --> 23:10.027
And the issue is actually stated very clearly in verse 13, for if you live according to the flesh, you will die.

23:10.728 --> 23:15.474
But if by the Spirit you put to death the deeds of the body, you will live.

23:16.275 --> 23:24.146
John Stott says, there is a kind of life that leads to death, and there is a kind of death that leads to life.

23:25.922 --> 23:28.586
Keep in mind the Paul is addressing believers.

23:30.348 --> 23:39.181
And the doctrine of the security of the believer does not eliminate the warnings of the Bible.

23:40.963 --> 23:41.885
Think Hebrews.

23:42.506 --> 23:45.069
See to it, the writer of the Hebrews says.

23:45.510 --> 23:50.838
See to it that you do not have a sinful, unbelieving heart that turns away from the living God.

23:51.318 --> 23:54.002
Now if you read that and say to yourself, I wonder who that's for?

23:55.298 --> 23:56.680
You've immediately made a mistake.

23:56.760 --> 23:58.702
It's for you, and it's for me.

23:59.603 --> 24:06.773
Later on, he says, we are not those who shrink back and are destroyed, but we are those who continue and are saved.

24:07.333 --> 24:11.779
That the ground of our relationship, the ground of our salvation is in the work of Christ.

24:12.199 --> 24:15.944
The evidence that we are in Christ is in our continuance.

24:17.006 --> 24:20.991
It's a long obedience in the same direction.

24:22.292 --> 24:23.634
We didn't mistake.

24:24.194 --> 24:33.084
a false sense of security in sin from a true experience of salvation from sin.

24:36.088 --> 24:37.970
I find that quite helpful.

24:39.111 --> 24:42.415
We are saved by grace through faith.

24:42.435 --> 24:48.082
And the reality of what he's urging us to hear is the very antithesis

24:48.194 --> 24:52.740
of a kind of mentality that I was exposed to as a young man in Scotland.

24:52.800 --> 24:58.727
And you may actually still be exposed to it, and I may be about to offend you as I pointed out.

24:59.668 --> 25:04.794
And it goes along these lines, let go and let God.

25:05.776 --> 25:08.098
It sounds really very spiritual, doesn't it?

25:08.479 --> 25:09.881
Well, there's not something I do.

25:10.201 --> 25:11.863
Let's let go and let God.

25:13.665 --> 25:17.650
But what Paul is actually saying here is not let go and let God.

25:18.114 --> 25:20.438
but is trust God and get going.

25:20.498 --> 25:22.261
Trust God and get going.

25:22.562 --> 25:36.786
I remember I spoke again at a conference a hundred years ago where the archetypal guy of let go and let go in the British Isles was the head of this operation and the girl who sang this song before I spoke

25:37.090 --> 25:46.902
I had this song, I don't know what it was, but it was something like, nothing for me to do, nothing for me to do, I have nothing to do, nothing to do.

25:47.363 --> 25:55.313
And I was sitting, my fingernails were biting into my hands because I was about to say the very reverse of what she was just singing about.

25:55.353 --> 25:59.698
Do you understand this?

26:00.194 --> 26:09.027
that the Spirit of God works within us to enable us to do cheerfully and joyfully that which the Word of God tells us to do.

26:09.067 --> 26:13.593
It's a delightful duty.

26:13.613 --> 26:20.082
I mean, it's like in married life, it is a privilege to serve one another.

26:21.004 --> 26:22.145
The reals are there.

26:22.185 --> 26:25.170
There's no doubt about that.

26:25.250 --> 26:28.274
We're not allowed to go beyond these boundaries.

26:29.346 --> 26:31.209
Because God knows what's best for us.

26:32.391 --> 26:33.592
And so he says, you do it.

26:34.373 --> 26:36.737
You keep your eyes to the front.

26:36.757 --> 26:38.460
You keep your gaze for your wife.

26:39.661 --> 26:48.695
Let her satisfy you all through the early days and into the middle days and then to the decrepitude days as they come.

26:49.837 --> 26:53.522
Because frankly, you don't look that good yourself.

26:57.186 --> 27:04.013
What he said in chapter 6 that we are set free from sin to become slaves of righteousness.

27:05.155 --> 27:10.240
Hence, the hymn writer, make me a captive lord, and then I shall be free.

27:10.300 --> 27:15.706
Force me to render up my sword, and I shall conquer be.

27:16.767 --> 27:26.898
I sink in life's alarms, when by myself I stand, imprison me within thine arms, and strong shall be.

27:27.202 --> 27:27.983
my stand.

27:28.564 --> 27:31.909
We're not to sit around waiting for God to take care of things.

27:31.989 --> 27:32.690
It's interesting.

27:33.231 --> 27:36.777
I've never had God turn the television off for me.

27:37.658 --> 27:40.062
I've never had God rip a novel out of my hands.

27:41.664 --> 27:43.527
I've never been propelled out of a cinema.

27:43.547 --> 27:45.390
I should never have gone in the first place.

27:46.591 --> 27:47.733
I don't expect him to.

27:48.514 --> 27:49.536
He gave me his word.

27:50.157 --> 27:51.239
He gave me his spirit.

27:52.901 --> 27:56.146
Because when we trust on a bay, we find that there's no other way.

27:56.834 --> 27:58.116
to be happy in Jesus.

27:59.298 --> 28:08.292
The Puritan says, let not that man think he makes any progress in holiness who walks not over the bellies of his lusts.

28:09.774 --> 28:17.185
Let not that man make any pretension of making progress in holiness who walks not over the bellies of his lusts.

28:17.245 --> 28:18.507
It's such a graphic picture.

28:18.788 --> 28:20.370
That's John Owen incidentally.

28:21.506 --> 28:23.268
Well, you say, well, what are you telling us here?

28:23.288 --> 28:24.889
Well, I'm not trying to tell you anything.

28:24.909 --> 28:32.477
I'm just trying to observe that in Christ our sinful inclinations have been dethroned, but they haven't been destroyed.

28:34.058 --> 28:34.278
Right?

28:35.720 --> 28:45.409
Well, I hope you're about to say right to that because if they have been destroyed and you wait for me afterwards because I need to find out how that happened.

28:45.429 --> 28:48.212
They've been dethroned, but they haven't been destroyed.

28:48.812 --> 28:50.514
That's why we have to deal with sin.

28:51.842 --> 28:53.104
That's why we have to deal with sin.

28:53.604 --> 28:55.187
That's why we've got to deal with it immediately.

28:55.307 --> 28:56.769
We've got to deal with it decisively.

28:57.009 --> 28:58.311
We've got to deal with it radically.

28:58.331 --> 29:00.113
We've got to deal with it consistently.

29:00.133 --> 29:03.057
And Jesus made that perfectly clear, didn't he?

29:03.498 --> 29:07.463
He said, you know, you could actually take one of your eyes out or chop one of your hands off.

29:07.924 --> 29:08.825
It would do you good.

29:09.626 --> 29:18.578
If that was going to be the difference between you entering the kingdom and continuing on your own way, if your hand causes you to sin, he said, why don't you take it off?

29:19.379 --> 29:19.840
Your eye.

29:20.581 --> 29:21.522
Fluck it out.

29:22.690 --> 29:24.652
And if you do this, you will live.

29:25.753 --> 29:31.219
Now, all of this, in verse 14, is tied to the fact of the relationship that we enjoy.

29:31.879 --> 29:45.493
The responsibility is bound up in the reality of what has happened in being united with Christ in dwelled by the Spirit and established on our way, 14.

29:46.234 --> 29:50.738
For all who are led by the Spirit of God are the sons of God.

29:51.906 --> 30:06.120
don't think in terms of being led by the Spirit of God as receiving subjective guidance, but rather think about being led by the Spirit of God in light of what he has just said in verse 13.

30:08.902 --> 30:21.074
For if you live according to the flesh, that's how we're led by saying no to that and saying to this to our sonship, the conflict with the flesh, incidentally, is a sign of sonship.

30:21.826 --> 30:27.836
Every so often when you're the pastor, somebody comes to you greatly disturbed because they've any may have committed the unpardonable sin.

30:28.797 --> 30:34.266
And we're able immediately to say to them, they're very fight that you showed up with a question, allows me to tell you that you haven't.

30:35.508 --> 30:39.374
Because if you had ever done such a thing, you wouldn't give a care in the world.

30:39.414 --> 30:40.896
You wouldn't be here to ask me about it.

30:41.537 --> 30:44.402
But the fight and the matter is, you recognize

30:44.642 --> 30:55.814
That as the Westminster Confession of Faith makes clear, the Christian is involved in a continual and irreconcilable war against the world and the flesh and the devil.

30:56.615 --> 31:07.106
And the work of the Holy Spirit in our lives is to bring us into conformity with God's Word is actually to conform us to the image of God's Son.

31:08.047 --> 31:14.354
So it makes sense, I think, that the same grace which reconciles us to God also antagonizes us

31:14.498 --> 31:15.319
to the evil one.

31:16.340 --> 31:23.949
That's why often people when they become new Christians, they say, but I thought everything would be plain sailing and it seems like everything is worse than it ever was before.

31:24.009 --> 31:28.193
It was actually much easier being a pagan than it was trying to follow Jesus.

31:28.494 --> 31:30.676
Well, that's because you just got involved in a battle.

31:31.317 --> 31:34.841
He never paid much attention to you before you were on his team.

31:35.241 --> 31:37.063
But you've been transferred out of that kingdom.

31:37.083 --> 31:38.425
You're living in a whole new place.

31:38.705 --> 31:40.787
You have a whole new captain of your salvation.

31:41.128 --> 31:43.090
Welcome, welcome to the war.

31:44.002 --> 31:46.125
And if you're worried about this, look at verse 15.

31:46.807 --> 31:57.243
You didn't receive the spirit of slavery to fall back into fear, but you've received the spirit of adoption as sons by whom we cry, Abba Father.

31:58.666 --> 32:03.474
Paul is reminding them of what has happened to them in their conversion.

32:04.655 --> 32:11.186
They didn't fall into a spirit of enslavement, but into the reality of adoption.

32:12.194 --> 32:22.610
Galatians 4, he says the same thing because your son's got to send the Spirit of his son into our hearts, crying Abba, Father.

32:24.093 --> 32:30.783
This is not servile fear, the fear of punishments that makes us question whether we belong.

32:32.145 --> 32:37.694
It is the filial fear that makes us wonder that we do belong.

32:39.577 --> 32:40.498
That's the wonder.

32:41.410 --> 32:50.862
my God has chosen me, though one of not, to sit beside my king in heaven's court."

32:50.882 --> 32:51.863
Again, the hymn writer.

32:53.064 --> 32:58.871
Now, some of you are very familiar with adoption, and so I want to explore the metaphor.

32:58.971 --> 33:10.866
It makes perfect sense, even by observation, if not by experience, adopted into God's family to bear his name, to

33:11.106 --> 33:22.203
inherit what he has promised to enjoy his affection and to reproduce his character.

33:23.605 --> 33:24.607
That's what he's doing.

33:27.671 --> 33:39.730
When you give your daughters away in marriage, as the fellow from California used to say, it's like giving your

33:39.970 --> 33:42.873
cries Stradivarius to a gorilla.

33:44.174 --> 33:57.928
And if I too engage it in my life to do that, and the inevitable question that comes when you essentially adopt your son-in-law is, what shall I call you?

34:01.012 --> 34:07.378
And I said, well, I'd like you to call me Dad, because I love you.

34:09.858 --> 34:18.486
and I would far rather you look to me in that way than you call me Alistair and certainly not by my middle name.

34:22.270 --> 34:30.919
But it would be utter presumption if I got out of my car in Chagrin and an unknown person walking down the street, a young fellow shouted out, Hey Dad!

34:32.540 --> 34:38.386
There would be no reason to turn around except to look for the person he was addressing.

34:39.778 --> 34:50.631
It would be presumption without a relationship, but given the relationship, there need be no hesitation, no hesitation.

34:50.651 --> 34:59.722
Haba is the Aramaic word you will recall that Jesus used in prayer, and he taught his disciples to do the same when you pray, say.

34:59.762 --> 35:09.554
And the intimacy that is conveyed in the reality of that relationship may reveal itself as much in heartache

35:10.146 --> 35:11.928
as it reveals in happiness.

35:13.349 --> 35:14.390
And I'll just end here.

35:16.032 --> 35:24.480
I think I immediately got this wrong by a song that went, Abba, Father, let me be yours and yours alone.

35:25.221 --> 35:28.945
Let my life forever be something along the line.

35:28.965 --> 35:31.267
It was a very lovely song, and I sang it a lot.

35:31.327 --> 35:38.194
And so I thought of it as immediately a declaration of devotion that it was.

35:38.370 --> 35:46.584
that it was, you could call them father or whatever, but when you call them Abba, you must be really engaged.

35:48.346 --> 35:58.002
And then I realized there are times in our lives when we don't even know how to pray.

36:01.568 --> 36:05.074
And all we can say is Abba.

36:06.914 --> 36:27.682
It's not so much an expression of devotion as it is a cry from the heart of a life redeemed to acknowledge that to be united with Christ, to be filled with the Spirit, to be encompassed by those who love us in the gospel is a privilege beyond privileges.

36:29.165 --> 36:36.114
And so we end by being able to look out on one another and say,

36:37.986 --> 36:42.691
What a funny bunch of people God has chosen to adopt.

36:42.711 --> 36:43.512
I mean, look at you.

36:45.675 --> 36:46.356
Look at me.

36:46.396 --> 36:52.222
I mean, the average church is not made of people that you like.

36:53.604 --> 36:56.687
The average church is made of people who are our natural enemies.

36:58.429 --> 37:02.514
It's not a group of people you would normally want to go on vacation with.

37:05.474 --> 37:08.960
I know that because my congregation wouldn't come on a vacation with me.

37:09.120 --> 37:10.161
I don't want to go with that either.

37:10.222 --> 37:12.125
It's the problem.

37:12.145 --> 37:13.667
I've mentioned many songwriters.

37:13.787 --> 37:15.390
It's Bill Gather's problem, isn't it?

37:16.171 --> 37:21.139
I'm so glad that you're part of the family of God, you know?

37:21.660 --> 37:22.241
No, I'm not.

37:22.261 --> 37:24.384
No, no.

37:24.724 --> 37:25.746
Listen, I want to say it.

37:26.067 --> 37:29.031
I'm surprised that you're part of the family of God.

37:30.013 --> 37:32.176
That God adopted you into his family.

37:32.276 --> 37:33.298
Can you believe it?

37:34.562 --> 37:36.684
He made us his own.

37:37.625 --> 37:42.189
And when we cry out to him, Abba, he knows the tone of our voice.

37:43.010 --> 37:45.052
He knows the circumstances of our lives.

37:45.632 --> 37:47.214
He knows the longings of our hearts.

37:47.714 --> 37:53.640
And he has the entire thing under control because there's no condemnation to us.

37:54.421 --> 38:04.210
And when we get there, before we get all, there is no separation for us either because of the wonder of the grace of God about which we've just been singing.

38:04.994 --> 38:06.576
Father, thank you for your word.

38:07.838 --> 38:10.843
Thank you that it is fixed in the heavens.

38:11.644 --> 38:14.929
Thank you that it is a lamp to our feet, a light to our path.

38:15.690 --> 38:34.738
We pray that you will help us as we ponder these things, as we seek to exhort and encourage one another, as we make our earthly journey towards our heavenly home in the sure and certain hope of the resurrection to eternal life through our Lord Jesus Christ.

38:35.618 --> 38:39.582
the one who changes our earthly bodies to be like unto His glorious body.

38:40.302 --> 38:46.068
According to the mighty working whereby He is able to seduce all things even death to Himself.

38:46.769 --> 38:49.671
And we pray, humbly, in Christ's name.

38:50.372 --> 38:50.713
Amen.

